<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Siemens Starts Joint Venture With Chinese Firm </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2903130994 Paris AFP in English 1256 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2903130994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Erlangen, Germany, March 29 (AFP) -- German 
industrial group Siemens has set up a joint venture with Chinese 
firm Machine Tool Electric Appliance Factory (SMTEAF) in Suzhou, 
eastern China, the German group announced on Tuesday. 
  It said the joint venture, to employ 1,400 people in an 
initial phase, would make low-voltage electricity distribution 
equipment. Investments will amount to 100 million marks over 
five years, the announcement said. 
  Siemens will hold a majority stake in the company, to be 
called Siemens Electrical Apparatus Ltd. 
  Siemens senior executive Carl-Heiner Thomas said the purpose 
of the joint venture is to commercialize Siemens technology on 
the Chinese market and acquire a larger presence on Southern 
Asian markets. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

