<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Maritime Traffic Pact Initialled With Romania </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903111194 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0957 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2903111194 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Germany and Romania have 
initialled a maritime traffic agreement. It is the first 
agreement of this kind between Romania and a West European state 
following the political changes in the country, the Federal 
Transport Ministry announced in Bonn today. The agreement was 
expected to provide an impetus for bilateral cooperation both 
commercially and at administrative level. It would regulate, 
among other things, the equal treatment of ships relating to 
their access to each other's ports, as well as port services, 
the recognition of seamen's travel documents and provisions in 
case of emergency. 

</TEXT>

