<H3> <TI>   Iran's Request for Compensation Viewed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2903080894 Istanbul HURRIYET in Turkish 25 Mar 94 p 18 </F>
<F P=103> NC2903080894 </F>
<F P=104>  Istanbul HURRIYET </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Iran has officially asked Turkey for compensation to 
help Tehran redeem the loss that country suffered when Turkish 
aircraft attacked the Zalah Camp in northern Iraq some time ago. 
The officials have not disclosed the amount of compensation 
Tehran has asked for to be able to hold talks on the matter. 
  It has been reported that Tehran has asked Ankara to pay 
separate remunerations for more than 10 people, who were 
wounded, and nine others, who were killed. Tehran has also 
asked for compensation for the damage that was caused by the 
attack. 
  Turkey will respond to Iran's request after the officials in 
Ankara consider the amount of compensation that has been asked 
for by Tehran. 
  Tehran's request probably will be discussed between the two 
countries. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

