<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Talks Held With Belgium's Claes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2903074894 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2903074894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Official talks have been held in Ankara with a view 
to developing the relations between Turkey and Belgium. 
  Belgian Foreign Minister Willy Claes who arrived in Ankara 
yesterday on an official visit met with Foreign Minister Hikmet 
Cetin. Later the delegations of the two countries headed by the 
respective foreign ministers held official talks. 
  In a statement after the talks, Cetin and Claes said that 
the 
political relations between the two countries were assessed. 
Cetin said that the talks were fruitful, and that he briefed 
the visiting foreign minister on the government's fight against 
terrorism, and its views on human rights and on the lifting of 
legislative immunity. Cetin added that they also discussed 
economic cooperation issues, Turkey's relations with the 
European Union and the Western European Union, and international 
questions. 
  Willy Claes pointed out that besides Bosnia-Herzegovina, 
there are problems in the Balkans that await solutions. He 
stressed that Turkey and Belgium agree in their assessments of 
regional issues and bilateral relations. He added that Belgium 
believes in the necessity for Turkey's territorial integrity. 
  President Suleyman Demirel received Claes at the Cankaya 
Mansion. 

</TEXT>

