<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Denktas Meets UN's Feissel, Comments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2903052494 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1530 GMT 28 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2903052494 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] President Rauf Denktas has said that UN 
officials are trying to impose the confidence-building measures 
package on the Turkish Cypriots by applying pressure. Denktas 
met with Gustave Feissel, the UN secretary general's assistant 
special envoy in Cyprus, at 1600 today. [passage omitted] 
  In a statement after the meeting, Denktas said that the 
Turkish Cypriot side is in favor of continuing the talks on the 
package. Denktas declared, however, that the UN officials are 
pressuring the Turkish Cypriot side to accept the package 
without even allowing it to assess the latest developments. 
Pointing out that additions have been made to the package, and 
topics that are not related to the package have been included in 
it, Denktas remarked that it is impossible to be forced to 
accept these proposals by a certain date. These proposals 
include matters concerning the guarantee issue, to which the 
Turkish Cypriot people are very sensitive, Denktas announced, 
stressing that it is out of the question for the Turkish Cypriot 
side to accept them. 
  Denktas explained that the Turkish Cypriot side underlined 
the flaws and shortcomings of the initial package, which Greek 
Cypriot Administration leader Glavkos Kliridhis said he would 
accept at the time. Some of these have since been resolved, 
Denktas added, noting: They were able to solve some of them. 
Therefore, we were not wrong. The rest they did not touch 
because the Greek Cypriot side is not willing to accept them. 
We do not accept this. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

