<H3> <TI>   Spokesman: Territorial Exchange Never Raised </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2903120794 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1030 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2903120794 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Government spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis has said 
the issue of territorial exchange has never been raised during 
the talks on the confidence-building measures. Kasoulidhis made 
his statement when he was asked to comment on a statement by a 
U.S. official to a Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation correspondent 
in New York in which he said the exchange of territory could 
provide an alternative to unobstructed access to Famagusta. 
  Kasoulidhis also said that the National Council will convene 
to make decisions as soon as there are developments. He also 
said the government has adopted its policy; it will await the UN 
secretary general's report. As soon as the report is issued, 
the spokesman added, the government will announce the steps it 
will take in coordination with the political leaders and Athens. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

