<H3> <TI>   Corekci Ends Visit to North Cyprus, Departs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2803150294 Nicosia KIBRIS in Turkish 24 Mar 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> NC2803150294 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia KIBRIS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] General Ahmet Corekci, deputy head of the Turkish 
General Staff, departed the TRNC [Turkish Republic of Northern 
Cyprus] at the end of his three-day visit, during which he 
inspected the Turkish Peace Force units. A military ceremony 
was held at Ercan Airport to see him off at 1700. Olgun 
Pasalar, deputy speaker of the TRNC Republican Assembly; Cahit 
Bayar, Turkey's ambassador in Nicosia; Lieutenant General Necati 
Ozgen, commander of the Turkish Peace Force units in the TRNC; 
Major General Attila Kurtaran, commander of the 28th Division; 
Major General Kadri Ozer, commander of the 39th Division; 
Brigadier General Yasar Spor, commander of the TRNC Security 
Forces; Gural Tanova, under secretary of the TRNC President's 
Office; Munir Muhtaroglu, under secretary of the Prime 
Minister's Office; and other military officials attended the 
ceremony. 

</TEXT>

