<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   EU's Van Den Broek Meets With Papandreou </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2803163094 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1500 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2803163094 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] After meeting Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou at 
Maximos Palace at noon today, Hans Van Den Broek, the European 
Union [EU] Commissioner in charge of foreign affairs, said the 
Greek Government has some good ideas on Skopje [The Former 
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia--FYROM] so the dialogue will 
continue under his own mediation. 
  Foreign Minister Karolos Papoulias participated in the 
meeting. He said that the efforts continue and added that he 
will meet the U.S. President's envoy in Skopje Matthew Nimetz 
and international mediator Cyrus Vance. He said: There are 
coordinated efforts to resolve the issue of Skopje. I hope 
there will be a significant outcome. 
  The EU commissioner said the EU is trying to find a formula 
to prepare the two sides to move closer. He said the EU is in a 
difficult position because of the Greek measures against Skopje, 
adding that these measures are against international law. The 
European Commission and the EU support Vance and Nimetz's 
efforts and will try to find a solution. Van Den Broek said the 
issue does not impact only Greece, but also peace and stability 
in the greater Balkan region. The commissioner said he is in 
contact with FYROM because Greece has some good ideas. 
  The European Commission will discuss Skopje after the Easter 
of the Catholics, which will be celebrated next Sunday [3 April]. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

