<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   EU Expatriates Protest Voter Registration Deadline </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2603164994 Paris AFP in English 2116 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2603164994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Paris, March 25 (AFP) -- Portuguese and Spanish 
expatriate groups here on Friday [25 March] protested the 
deadline given by France to European Union [EU] nationals to 
register for a vote in June's European elections. 
  European Union rules give EU citizens the right to vote and 
be elected in member countries other than their own, on 
condition of residency. 
  The Portuguese association in France (CCPF) and the 
Federation of Spanish Emigre Associations in France, called for 
the registration period to be extended from April 15 to the end 
of April. 
  With 700,000 emigres in France, the Portuguese are the 
largest EU grouping living as expatriates in France, ahead of 
both the Italians and Spanish. 

</TEXT>

