<H3> <TI>   Warns on `Reactionary Right' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2803205294 Milan Canale 5 Television Network in Italian 
2018 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2803205294 </F>
<F P=104>  Milan Canale 5 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Northern League Leader Umberto Bossi by </F>
unidentified correspondent -- live] 
  [Excerpts] [Bossi] The figures are more or less what one 
could have expected, at least what we expected. Now we have to 
see how many seats we have, how many parliamentarians we have. 
I think we can say that we can govern with the Freedom 
Alliance, but bearing in mind that for years the League has 
guaranteed democracy in the country, and it will have to assess 
how to prevent the reactionary right from getting through, so we 
want to understand things well. [sentence as heard] First, see 
the programs, then undertstand with whom and how, in short, a 
government can be formed. [passage omitted] 
  We have a general indication that the Freedom Alliance has 
won, together with the MSI [Italian Social Movement], i.e., the 
vote that comes from the south which will reopen the North's 
wallet, in short. So, you will understand we have to understand 
each other to assess whether there is space for an agreement for 
government. [passage omitted] 
  [Correspondent] Do you see a reactionary right wing? 
  [Bossi] Yes, there it is with 12 percent given to the MSI. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

