<H3> <TI>   Left-Wing Leader D'Alema Views Results </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2803215194 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 2139 GMT 
28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2803215194 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] "The most important thing is the structural collapse 
of the center, balanced by a shift to the right of the old power 
blocks," according to Massimo D'Alema, [deputy Leader of 
Democratic Party of the Left]. "Maybe we hoped that the old 
power block had fallen apart. However, it merged with the 
forces of the right," he added. 
  "I think that in the end there will not be a majority 
capable 
of governing. I think that we will have to work for a 
constituent government." 

</TEXT>

