Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Foreign Ministry Advises Against </F>
Traveling To Algeria"] 
  [Text] The Belgian Foreign Ministry issued an advisory on 
Friday [25 March] that anyone intending to travel to Algeria 
should postpone the trip until later, unless it is of the utmost 
urgency. 
  The Ministry confirmed its concern for "individual security 
problems in Algeria," and asked Belgians who had not yet been 
able to leave Algeria to "make every possible effort to 
guarantee their safety as much as possible and to keep in 
regular contact with the Belgian Embassy in Algiers." 

