<H3> <TI>   PRC Justice Minister Visits, Holds Talks </TI></H3>
<H4>   Views Human Rights, DPRK With Kinkel </H4>
<F P=102> LD2903120794 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1121 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2903120794 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- German Foreign Minister Klaus 
Kinkel (FDP) has urged the Chinese Government to enforce human 
rights in the People's Republic. Without political reform and 
developments towards a fair legal system, the economic reforms 
in China would reach their limits, Kinkel warned during talks 
with Chinese Justice Minister Yang Xiao in Bonn today, according 
to the Foreign Ministry. 
  Kinkel also underlined the German government's willingness 
to 
provide support in all areas which would serve to develop a 
system based on the rule of law in the People's Republic. The 
foreign minister also called on the Chinese government to use 
its influence on North Korea and to do everything to prevent a 
military conflict. The North Korean nuclear issue had to be 
solved within the framework of the Nuclear Non-Proliferation 
Treaty. 

</TEXT>

