<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Expect 40-Percent Tariff Reduction </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2903163994 Paris AFP in English 1538 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2903163994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Geneva, March 29 (AFP) -- The Uruguay Round of 
trade negotiations under GATT will produce a higher than 
expected global tariff reduction of 40 percent for traded goods, 
trade diplomats said here Tuesday [29 March]. 
  This is seven percentage points in excess of the initial 
objective of 33 percent for tariff cutting under the 
seven-year-old negotiations, to be finalized in two weeks by a 
GATT (General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade) ministerial 
conference at Marrakesh, Morocco. 
  The 40 percent overall reduction in customs duties will be 
formally announced in a draft declaration to be adopted by 
ministers from about 120 countries at Marrakesh. 
  Trade negotiators here said the tariff-cutting excercise was 
completed when a number of countries tabled their final market 
access offers here on Monday after intensive bilateral talks 
since the Final Act of the Uruguay Round was adopted here last 
December 15. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

