<H3> <TI>   WEU Secretary General's Mandate Extended </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR2803120294 Brussels BELGA in French 1422 GMT 27 Mar 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2803120294 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels BELGA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article signed JCH/LVE: "European Union -- Wim Van </F>
Eeckelen's Mandate Extended for Six Months"; as released by 
Brussels BELGA Database] 
  [Text] Ioannina, 27 Mar (BELGA) -- Belgian Foreign Minister 
Willy Claes announced that the foreign ministers of the Twelve 
on Sunday [27 March] agreed to extend by six months the mandate 
of Netherlander Wim Van Eeckelen as general secretary of the 
Western European Union [WEU]. 
  Foreign Ministry sources say that four candidates are 
already 
knocking at the door to succeed him. 
  An official stated that current Luxembourg Foreign Minister 
Jacques Poos has expressed an interest in the job, thus somewhat 
reducing the chances of former Belgian Foreign Minister Mark 
Eyskens. 
  A Portuguese candidate, Mr. Coutilheiro, author of a peace 
plan for the former Yugoslavia, and another Italian candidate 
are also in the race. 

</TEXT>

