<H3> <TI>   Bonn Welcomes Acceptance of EU Voting Compromise </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2903192894 Hamburg DPA in German 1736 GMT 29 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2903192894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- The FRG Government has explicitly 
welcomed the fact that all the partners have agreed to the 
proposal on the question of a blocking minority in an enlarged 
European Union [EU]. 
  "The adoption of this compromise proposal now clears the 
road 
for the planned enlargement of the EU by Austria, Sweden, 
Finland, and Norway on 1 January 1995 from the point of view of 
the 12 member states," it is stated in a statement released by 
Deputy Government Spokesman Norbert Schaefer in Bonn on Tuesday 
[29 March]. 

</TEXT>

