<H3> <TI>   Kinkel Asks PRC To Influence DPRK </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2903115294 Hamburg DPA in German 1109 GMT 29 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2903115294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- FRG Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel 
(Free Democratic Party of Germany) wants the Chinese Government 
to use its influence on Pyongyang in the controversy over North 
Korea's nuclear program. In a talk with Chinese Justice 
Minister Xiao Yang on Tuesday [29 March], Kinkel also pointed to 
China's responsibility as a permanent member of the UN Security 
Council. Pyongyang refuses to have its nuclear facilities 
inspected by the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA). 
  At the meeting, Kinkel insisted on the observation of human 
rights in China, a spokesman announced after the meeting. The 
minister emphatically referred to a special human rights case in 
connection with the students' unrest of 1989, in which there has 
still not been any reaction despite repeated requests by Kinkel. 
  The FRG Foreign Minister also advocated a "fair autonomy and 
the protection of the cultural, ethnic, and religious rights" of 
the Tibetans. 

</TEXT>

