<H3> <TI>   Police Step Up Security Near Israeli Embassy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2903184394 Hamburg DPA in German 1644 GMT 29 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2903184394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- On Tuesday [29 March] the police 
increased their protective measures for "Israeli objects" in 
Bonn. Among other things, the police closed the main 
thoroughfare where the Israeli Embassy is located. In the next 
few days, residents will have to identify themselves if they 
want to get to their houses. Normal traffic is being diverted 
on a large scale. According to the police, the German security 
authorities have been given tip-offs that Israeli "objects" 
might become targets of terrorist attacks. 

</TEXT>

