<H3> <TI>   Andreatta Welcomes Lithuania-Poland Accord </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR2903143794 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1230 GMT 29 
Mar 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2903143794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Andreatta on Lithuania-Poland </F>
Friendship Accord"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, March 29 -- Italian Foreign Minister 
Beniamino Andreatta, in his role as duty chairman of the 
Conference on Security and Cooperation in Europe, has expressed 
his pleasure over the recent inking of a friendship and 
cooperation agreement between Lithuania and Poland, according to 
a Farnesina [Foreign Ministry] communique today. 
  Such an agreement is an example of how misunderstandings of 
the past can be overcome in a framework of cooperation and in a 
European spirit so as to give a new positive dimension to 
bilateral relations among neighboring countries, according to 
Andreatta. 
  The accord can be seen as fully ensconced within the 
framework of fundamental CSCE principles and constitutes an 
important contribution to security and stability in the entire 
region, the communique added. 

</TEXT>

