<H3> <TI>   Balladur Drops 12 Points in Opinion Poll </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR3003121694 Paris LE QUOTIDIEN DE PARIS in French 30 Mar 94 
p 4 </F>

<F P=103> BR3003121694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris LE QUOTIDIEN DE PARIS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The French people's confidence in Prime Minister 
Balladur registered a 12-point drop in March, according to the 
CSA-"La Vie" opinion poll. Of those interviewed (between the 
two cantonal election rounds), 40 percent have confidence in 
Edouard Balladur's capacity "to cope efficiently with the main 
problems the country is facing," while 45 percent think 
otherwise. Meanwhile, Francois Mitterrand's rating indicates 
an opposite trend, with 45 percent of those responding with 
positive appraisals against 39 percent negative. This is the 
first time since March 1993 that the head of state leads his 
prime minister in a poll. 

</TEXT>

