<H3> <TI>   Fini Backs Berlusconi for Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903163794 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1615 GMT 
29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2903163794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Gianfranco Fini is optimistic that a new government 
will be formed quickly. He has not put himself forward for the 
office of prime minister but is backing Silvio Berlusconi, and 
has ruled out Northern League politicians. He has pointed out 
that the League is only present in some areas of Italy. 
  After stressing that he has not spoken to Umberto Bossi on 
the telephone, either yesterday or today, Fini asked the 
Northern League leader to be completely frank about the value of 
national unity and solidarity between the north and the south, 
which is fundamental to the National Alliance. He also pointed 
out that Berlusconi's bid to be prime minister is in keeping 
with the results of the election. 

</TEXT>

