<H3> <TI>   Awaits Outcome of Discussions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903194494 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1745 
GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2903194494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Due Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Gianfranco Fini is once again confronting the 
eternal triangle of himself, Silvio Berlusconi, and the other 
man, Umberto Bossi, who is continually raising the stakes for a 
possible pact. Fini is maintaining his usual calm, even if he 
has said that Bossi is not fit to be prime minister. He has 
pointed out that although the National Alliance has accepted 
decentralization, it will continue to defend Italian unity. He 
is awaiting the outcome of the patient tactics of Silvio 
Berlusconi, the spinner of webs. 
  [Begin Fini recording] I believe that at this stage it is up 
to Berlusconi, who has obtained the most votes, to set up a 
series of meetings. We met this afternoon and discussed the 
tremendous election results. We discussed the fact that 
Italians have chosen who they want to govern them. I believe 
that in the next few days Berlusconi will also meet Bossi, after 
which we will meet again. There will certainly be two of us 
present -- I do not know if there will be three people at the 
meeting. As far as we are concerned, the problems connected 
with the Northern League remain the same: We want an absolute 
guarantee that Italy remains united and a policy of solidarity 
between north and south. [end recording] 
  [Announcer] Fini warned, however, that without Bossi they 
would not have sufficient numbers to form a government. 

</TEXT>

