<H3> <TI>   South Tirol Party Opposes National Alliance Coalition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903161494 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1625 GMT 
29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2903161494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] "The Sudtirol Volks Partei [South Tirol Peoples 
Party, SVP] will not support any government that includes the 
National Alliance." The statement was released by the executive 
committee of the SVP, which met in Bolzano to examine the 
results of the election. 
  According to the SVP, the success of the right on a national 
level represented a "heavy burden, whose dimensions are not yet 
clear." 
  SVP President Brugger, who was reelected to the Chamber of 
Deputies, said : "As an ethnic minority, we are expecting to 
face hard times in Rome." 

</TEXT>

