<H3> <TI>   Committee: Joint EU Defense Cannot Be Forced </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903171794 Stockholm Radio Sweden in Swedish 1545 GMT 29 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2903171794 </F>
<F P=104>  Stockholm Radio Sweden </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Swedish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sweden can never be forced to take part in joint 
defense in the EU [European Union], the Standing Committee on 
Foreign Affairs of the Riksdag says. The committee points out 
that the agreement of all EU countries is necessary for a joint 
EU defense. All Riksdag parties, except the Left Party, agree 
with the committee's view. 

</TEXT>

