<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Special Coordinator Lamb Arrives for Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2903163294 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1400 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2903163294 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Robert Lamb, the U.S. State Department special 
coordinator on the Cyprus issue, arrived in Cyprus this 
afternoon aiming to give a new push to the proximity talks on 
the confidence-building measures [CBM's]. 
  In an arrival statement at Larnaca Airport, Lamb said that 
he 
is not bringing any new proposals on the CBM's, adding that he 
believes there are many ideas on the negotiating table. He said 
his goal is to see whether he can assist in bridging the current 
differences. 
  In response to a question, Lamb said he did not come to 
Cyprus to put pressure on one or the other side. 

</TEXT>

