<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kliridhis Expects `Nothing' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2903163494 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1500 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2903163494 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In an exclusive statement to the Cyprus Broadcasting 
Corporation, President Glavkos Kliridhis said the Cypriot 
Government will not proceed with any action before the UN 
secretary general submits his report to the Security Council. 
Kliridhis added that he does not expect anything from his 
meeting tomorrow with Robert Lamb, the U.S. State Department 
special coordinator on the Cyprus issue. 
  The president said there is nothing new to justify the 
convening of a National Council meeting. He added: When there 
is, I will convene it. Asked whether he will stop over in 
Athens upon his return from Strasbourg where he will address the 
Council of Europe parliamentary assembly, Kliridhis said this 
will depend on his schedule. 

</TEXT>

