<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkes: People Want Coalition To Remain </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2903132894 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 
GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2903132894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Nationalist Action Party [NAP] leader Alparslan 
Turkes has said that the NAP emerged from the local elections 
with great success because of its consistent and stable policies 
focused on unity and the integrity of the country. 
  At a news conference he held in parliament, Turkes said that 
even though certain circles expected the NAP to weaken because 
some deputies had left it, the party increased its votes in 
municipal councils by 250 percent and the number of its mayors 
by 300 percent, to 155. 
  Turkes said that the citizens in eastern and southeastern 
Turkey showed in the elections that they do not want to secede. 
He added: The election results are a good lesson to those who 
try to interfere in Turkey's domestic affairs. 
  Turkes pointed out that the NAP received good results in 
eastern and southeastern Anatolia. He said: The elections were 
held in a mature way, with a high rate of participation. They 
resulted in a victory for democracy. 
  The NAP leader stated that the citizens voted in favor of 
maintaining the coalition, adding: The election results show 
that the people do not want chaos, or the state business to be 
delayed through frequent elections. They show that the people 
want the present coalition to remain power. That is my 
conclusion. 

</TEXT>

