<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   RP Candidate Wins Mayoral Election in Ankara </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2903172694 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1530 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2903172694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Mar. 29 (A.A.) -- The Pro-Islamic 
Prosperity Party (RP) won the Ankara mayoral election, according 
to the latest unofficial results on Tuesday [30 March]. 
  Melih Gokcek, the RP candidate won by a narrow margin over 
Social Democrat Populist Party (SHP) candidate Korel Goymen. 
  The RP made sweeping gains across the country to take third 
place overall behind Prime Minister Tansu Ciller's center-right 
True Path Party (DYP) and the main opposition Motherland Party 
(ANAP). 
  The RP doubled its share of the vote since the last 
nationwide municipal elections in 1989. 
  Campaigning for a "just order" and adherence to conservative 
Islamic values, the RP has found support among the rural 
migrants who flocked to the major cities in search of jobs. 
  The party has never made a serious impact in Ankara, a city 
of 3 million and cradle of the secular Turkish Republic founded 
by Mustafa Kemal Ataturk in 1923. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

