<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   RP, TPP Supporters Clash in Agri, 5 Die </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2903161294 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1600 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2903161294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Patnos, Agri Mar. 29 (A.A.) -- The death toll rose 
to five following the clash that broke out between supporters of 
two separate parties in Patnos, Agri earlier on Tuesday [29 
March]. 
  The incident broke out when supporters of the True Path 
Party 
(DYP) mayoral candidate Ihsan Hallac, who won the election, 
celebrated and marched through the town. 
  As they were passing in front of the Prosperity Party (RP) 
campaign office, angry shouting broke out which quickly turned 
into an armed clash. 
  Among those killed was the RP mayoral candidate Fahrettin 
Esin including two members of his family. 
  A curfew was imposed in the city, while a large number of 
people were detained. 

</TEXT>

