<AU>   FBIS-WEU-94-061 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  29 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   17 Captured for Collaboration With `Terrorists' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2903163694 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1605 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2903163694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Aydin, Mar. 29 (A.A.) -- Seventeen people were 
captured in Aegean province of Aydin including five members of 
the Democracy Party (DEP), on the grounds that they were 
involved in a number of terrorist activities, it was reported on 
Tuesday [29 March]. 
  A statement from Aydin Governor's Office said that during 
operations carried out by security forces 17 were captured, 
among them DEP representative in Aydin and another senior 
official of the party. 
  It was determined all had taken part in terrorist activities 
such as the killing of a civilian, outlawed propaganda prior to 
the local elections, and extortion, forcing shops to close down 
as well as providing logistic and material help for a terrorist 
organization. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-20385 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu061_q_94008" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-WEU-94-061 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  29 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

