<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Considering Government Reshuffle </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2903200894 Athens I KATHIMERINI in Greek 29 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC2903200894 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens I KATHIMERINI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou will reshuffle the 
government after the PASOK [Panhellenic Socialist Movement] 
congress and before the European Parliament elections, to wage 
the election battle with the "confidence" of a renewed 
government. According to reliable sources, he believes some 
correctional changes are necessary to give new impetus to the 
sectors that are not functioning well and to deal with the 
problem of lack of coordination within the government. 
  According to the same sources, the prime minister intends to 
give a portfolio to Dhimitrios Tsovolas and replace Education 
Minister Dhimitrios Fatouros. 
  He is also considering whether he should remove Alternate 
Foreign Minister Theodhoros Pangalos during the shuffle or after 
the expiration of the Greek European Union presidency in July. 
  The situation at the top of the National Economy Ministry 
will remain unchanged unless Finance Minister Yeoryios 
Yennimatas decides to move up to the government's vice 
presidency or resign. In this case, his replacement will be 
either Bhouttos, Vaitsos, or Pottakis. 

</TEXT>

