<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   EU Agrees on Koschnick as Mostar Administrator </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2703151994 Hamburg DPA in German 1957 GMT 26 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2703151994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Ioannina (DPA) -- On Saturday [26 March], at 
their meeting in Ioannina in northwestern Greece, the foreign 
ministers of the European Union agreed on assigning Hans 
Koschnick with heading the reconstruction in Mostar, the capital 
of Herzegovina. The former Social Democratic mayor of Bremen 
and internal affairs senator had been suggested by the Federal 
Government as head of the European Union administration of the 
town, which has been tortured by the war. This was stated by 
FRG Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel on the sidelines of the 
deliberations in Ioannina. 
  FRG Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel has already phoned 
Koschnick. The former Bremen mayor has accepted the offer. 
Details must still be clarified, Kinkel said. The ministers' 
decision must now be formally confirmed at the next meeting of 
the chief diplomats in Luxembourg on 18 April. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

