<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   SDPP Claims Elections `Tainted' With Fraud </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA3003110994 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 0920 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA3003110994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Ankara, Mar. 30 (A.A.) -- Social Democratic 
Populist Party [SDPP] Secretary General Metin Culhaoglu said on 
Tuesday [29 March] that Turkey has never witnessed such a moral 
flaw in the election system. 
  "These elections have been tainted," Culhaoglu said. 
  In a statement from his party's headquarters, Culhaoglu said 
that they have received claims that the results of local polls 
have been distorted. 
  He said that they have received great numbers of ballots 
casted for his party that were found in trash cans and that they 
found a printing house in the central Anatolian city of Kayseri 
which was printing ballots. 
  Culhaoglu said that the SDPP applied to the Prosecutor's 
Office, claiming fraud and petitioned the High Election Board. 
  "Fraud claims are pouring in from all over the country," he 
said. "These claims show that an organized action has been 
carried out throughout the country." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

