<H3> <TI>   French Troops Leave for Zagreb To Relieve Unit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU3103111894 Paris AFP in English 1104 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU3103111894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lille, France, March 31 (AFP) -- A contingent of 
200 French troops left the northern French city of Lille for 
Zagreb Thursday [31 March] to relieve the 403d Logistical 
Support Detachment whose term of service in the former 
Yugoslavia is due to expire. 
  The contingent, the first of three totalling 600 troops to 
leave for Zagreb over a three-day period, is headed by 
Lieutenant-Colonel Patrick Rose. 
  France has a total of more than 6,000 men in the former 
Yugoslavia. 

</TEXT>

